  <ol>
    <li><strong>Summary of MyCorner Services/ Orders</strong>
      <ol>
        <li>Store will be provided with one or more custom accounts (Accounts) personal to the Store.</li>
        <li>MyCorner will host the Account(s).</li>
        <li>Features include:
          <ul>
            <li>Hosted Account providing marketing/advertising opportunities</li>
            <li>Online Ordering by customers for pickup or delivery</li>
            <li>Data/Analytics</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Customer Obligations/Content</strong>
          <ol>
            <li>Store Content: name, address, contact information, hours of operation, goods for sale, store photograph.</li>
            <li>Store is responsible for the content it posts and goods it sells.</li>
            <li>Store is responsible for keeping its inventory up to date.</li>
            <li>Store may reject any order in its sole discretion in compliance with applicable law</li>
            <li>Store is responsible for ensuring legal requirements are met. For example, if the goods (e.g., tobacco or alcoholic beverages) ordered require the consumer to be of a certain age or meet any other legal or Store restrictions, Store is responsible for checking and verifying this information.</li>
          </ol>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Fees</strong>
          <ol>
            <li>All payments are processed through Stripe.</li>
            <li>Fees (all fees are on a per order basis):
              <ol>
                <li>Fixed - $0.29 (Stripe fee, per transaction)</li>
                <li>Variable - 6% of order total, as follows:
                  <ol>
                    <li>15% Stripe fee</li>
                    <li>85% MyCorner fee</li>
                  </ol>
                </li>
                <li>Fees are based on the overall order price</li>
                <li>Sales tax: Stores are responsible for setting sales tax during onboarding and collecting sales tax on orders, where applicable.</li>
                <li>Payments are made by Store&rsquo;s customer to Store Account through Stripe; MyCorner then collects Fees from the Store through Stripe.</li>
                <li>Payments are placed on hold when an order is placed and captured when the Store completes the order.</li>
                <li>Refunds/Adjustments to Fees: determined on a case by case basis.</li>
                <li>Penalty fee: Incomplete Orders that are reported completed by the Store are subject to penalty fees. When an order is placed, Store may accept or reject the order. After store accepts an order, it may cancel the order, but such cancellations will incur a penalty fee as follows: Store may cancel up to 5% of orders; any cancellations above 5% of orders will incur a penalty fee of 5% of order total (up to $5.00), per order.</li>
                <li>Fees will begin taking effect after the first 100k in transaction volume through the platform</li>
              </ol>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </li>
      </ol>
